description: NBC News’ Janis Mackey Frayer reports on the latest details from Pope Francis’ trip to Indonesia including a symbolic visit to the biggest mosque in Indonesia where both the Pope and the grand imam issued a joint statement on climate change.
title: Pope Francis and Indonesia’s grand imam issue a joint statement on climate change

description: U.K. prosecutors said they had discontinued indecent assault charges against former Hollywood producer Harvey Weinstein.
title: Harvey Weinstein indecent assault case ended by U.K. prosecutors

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin said Thursday that Ukraine’s gamble to seize his country's territory has backfired by boosting his own military's advance, a boast he paired with teasing support for Vice President Kamala Harris in the upcoming U.S. election.
title: Freewheeling Putin opines on Kamala Harris' laugh and Russia’s ‘sacred duty’

description: Hamas' hostage killings and an increasingly hardline public stance from Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu have complicated the United States' push for a cease-fire in Gaza, a senior Biden administration official has said.
title: Hamas' hostage killings and Netanyahu's hardline stance complicate cease-fire deal

description: Dozens of African leaders have descended on Beijing for a summit that signals China's influence in a continent that it hopes will be a key ally. Chinese President Xi Jinping proposed bilateral relations with all African countries that have diplomatic ties with China be upgraded to the "strategic" level.
title: Chinese President Xi proposes elevation of China-Africa relations

description: China’s main intelligence agency has a warning for young people: Beware of “handsome guys” and “beautiful women” looking to turn them into spies.
title: Beware ‘beautiful women’ and ‘handsome guys’ who want to turn you into spies, China warns

description: A judge ordered the release of a former U.S. Green Beret indicted in connection with a failed 2020 coup attempt against Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro.
title: Ex-Green Beret behind failed Venezuela raid released pending trial on weapons charges

description: Pope Francis and the grand imam of Southeast Asia’s largest mosque vowed to unite against religiously motivated violence in a joint declaration on Thursday.
title: Pope urges fight against extremism and climate change at Southeast Asia’s largest mosque

description: Pope Francis visited Indonesia, becoming the first pope to visit the country in 35 years. His visit is part of his four-nation trip through Southeast Asia and Oceania. During his visit he urged Indonesia to fight religious intolerance and violence.
title: Pope Francis visits Indonesia, the first visit by a pope in 35 years
